name: APPLE 5-A-DAY FRUIT STICKER POSTER
description:
Each of these A1-size litho-printed posters depicts a piece of fruit graphically constructed using the negative space of a fruit sticker.

It is a simple idea. Next time you have a juicy Cox apple or a crunchy Comice pear, instead of putting the sticker under your desk or customising the side of your monitor, fill in the gaps on the poster from the fruit that you've eaten that day.

We’ve even thrown in a few sweets giving you the perfect excuse for that Kit-Kat.

name: Dyslexic eye chart
description:
Why should people who can read big words have all the fun? 
Brighten your wall with the dyslexic eye chart featuring a smorgasbord of animals from the blue whale to the gnat.
Silk screened and printed on 350 gsm paper with a limited run of 100.
